
@startuml

class User {
  -id: String
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
}

class Account {
  -accountNumber: String
  -accountType: String (Personal / Business)
  +createPage(pageName: String): Page
}

class PersonalAccount {
  +sendFriendRequest(toUser: User): void
  +acceptFriendRequest(fromUser: User): void
}

class BusinessAccount {
  -monthlyFee: Double
  +createAdPage(pageName: String): AdPage
}

class Page {
  -pageName: String
  -visits: Integer
  +grantPrivilege(account: Account): void
}

class AdPage {
  -bounceRate: Double
  -clickThroughRate: Double
  -conversionRate: Double
}

User "1" --> "1" Account
Account "1" --> "0..*" Page
Account "1" --> "0..1" User
Page "1" --> "1" Account
Page "1" --> "0..*" Account (granted privileges)

note right of Page
  Only personal accounts can be granted privileges to pages.
end note

note right of BusinessAccount
  Business accounts can create ad pages with metrics.
end note

note right of PersonalAccount
  Only personal accounts can send/receive friend requests.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Relationships and Features:
- **User** has a unique ID and fills out a form to register.
- **Account** is created per user, with a unique account number. It can be either **Personal** or **Business**.
- A **User** can have only one **Account** (either personal or business), as per Facepage's Terms of Use.
- **PersonalAccount** allows sending and receiving friend requests.
- **BusinessAccount** incurs a monthly fee and can create **AdPages**.
- **Page** is managed by exactly one **Account**, but **PersonalAccounts** can be granted privileges to other pages.
- **AdPage** is a special type of **Page** that tracks marketing metrics.

